Caption: Life is too short for bad meetings. Follow these 4 simple rules to keep all your team meetings focused efficient and productive! ?ëá1Ô∏è‚É£ Always provide a clear and concise agenda beforehandThis sets up expectations allows preparation and gives a clear focus for everyone in attendance.Meetings with set agendas tend to be 44% more productive! (Lucid Meetings Survey)2Ô∏è‚É£ Keep meetings as short as possible and time-box agenda itemsLonger meetings often lead to diminished attention and surprise surprise are not necessarily more productive.Attention spans drop sharply after about 10-18 minutes of a presentation. (University of Nebraska study)3Ô∏è‚É£ Ensure the right people are in the meetingInvolving people who arent directly impacted can waste time and resources.Employees stated they spent 31 hours each month in unproductive meetings often because they didnt need to be there. (Atlassian)4Ô∏è‚É£ Assign clear action items and follow-upsTaking this action ensures accountability and tracks meeting outcomes.71% of senior managers said meetings are unproductive and inefficient without clear next steps. (Harvard Business Review)What are your best tips for keeping meetings productive?Drop your ideas in the comments! ?í≠#calendly #meetings
